A place of historical and archaeological importance
It's a quaint temple with a four-tiered pagoda-shaped roof and a doorway that is adorned with carvings of mythological figures and symbols
A part of the northern end of the Kullu Valley, it is situated by the Beas river at a height of 1,926 m above sea level
Explore the charming old town of Manali on foot, or try paragliding over its rolling green slopes and apple orchards
The speciality of this region, the Kullu trout fish, is relished by locals and visitors